wikipedia_page.main: Henry Denison (born 2 June 1810, Ossington, Nottinghamshire; died 30 November 1858, Ossington) was an English cricketer who was associated with Oxford University Cricket Club and made his first-class debut in 1829.Denison was educated at Eton and Christ Church, Oxford. He was a fellow of All Souls College, Oxford, 1831–40. He studied law at Lincoln's Inn and was called to the bar in 1835.
